1. make
2. make install
4. wmfishtime &

Version 1.2 includes automatic mail-spool check. Periodically, wmfishtime
will check for new contents in the file pointed to by $MAIL variable. This
is disabled by default, but can be enabled using "-c" or "--check-mail"
options.

If you get a gray box and nothing else after you start this dockapp, you
have a retarded broken window manager such as E, recent versions of the KDE
window manager, etc. Remember that if you get this your system totally sucks
ass, and you have to use "-b" or "--broken" options to fix this. If you feel
offended by this, make sure and let developers of E and KWM know that they
suck.
